The number of children from Eastern European countries in British schools is increasing, causing concern among the remaining people about the evolution of local education.
The integration of Eastern Europeans is currently facing a series of obstacles.
British schools even see cases where conflicts between immigrants and descendants of the original inhabitants turn into violence.
