Cuba, the most beautiful island in the Caribbean
For visitors, it is truly an island of freedom.
Everything you expect from your vacation can be achieved if you make the right choice.
Golden and white beaches like snow, high waves or a calm sea like a pond.
Palm trees and all inclusive with waiters offering you a pizza, ice cream or intoxicating cocktails on the beach.
Kitesurfing, golf and roulette.
On the islands of the Caribbean Sea, you will not find this list only in its entirety, but enriched.
Now, there is only one island on which you will find much more and that is Cuba, the largest and most beautiful island in the Greater Antilles.
At the time of the Spanish, Cuba had been the stronghold of their invasion of America.
Christopher Columbus called it the most beautiful place the human eye has ever seen.
Havana became the depository and transshipment place of the treasures that the Spaniards had stolen and transported to Europe.
Then came the American era.
The Hotel Nacional was built at the beginning of the 20's.
It was Lucky Luciano, one of the heads of the American mafia, who built it, since everything that was a crime in the US (especially under prohibition) was admitted and supported in Cuba: drugs, gambling, prostitution.
Among his clients were, among others,
Winston Churchill, Ava Gardner, Frank Sinatra.
In Havana, high buildings grew and cars, belonging to the cult symbols of the 50's of the last century, circulated on the wide boulevards.
Ernest Hemingway bought a property in San Francisco de Paula, near Havana, and in Cojímar he owned his yacht.
Show business stars and politicians from all over America left their signatures on the walls of the Bodeguita del Medio.
What about today?
You can leave your autograph on the walls of the Bodeguita of Havana.
In the bar of the Hotel Nacional, a luxury hotel, you will be mixed the cocktail of your choice.
And these cult cars still circulate in Havana, since the jigoulis and fiats once imported have already rotted for a long time, in such a salty and humid climate.
Although Havana, especially the oldest part, is substantially decaying, nowhere else in the vicinity are there as many splendid colonial monuments as there are precisely there.
Other places become more beautiful, such as Trinidad.
Since tourism brings the money if necessary, its development has the green light.
In the last fifteen years, new hotels have grown not only in Havana, but especially in Varader, on the coast of Holguín province, and also on the small islands such as Cayo Coco, Cayo Guillermo and others.
Cuba still offers a fantasy that is unique in the world and that will be appreciated especially by lovers of small trains.
The cane had returned from the extended plantations in the sweet shops on a narrow track by small steam and engine trains.
Their rolling stock has not been renewed for decades and this is how you can see small locomotives running, whose contemporaries are not elsewhere only in museums.
Where to direct your steps?
The majority of visitors do not miss the most well-known places.
There is no need to write much about Varadero or Havana.
