Koloniální <0xC5><0xA1>pan<0xC4><0x9B>lská architecture,výrazn<0xC4><0x9B> ovlivn<0xC4><0x9B>ná pozd<0xC4><0x9B>j<0xC5><0xA1>ími francouzskými osadníky, se za <0xC4><0x8D>ty<0xC5><0x99>i staletí tem<0xC4><0x9B><0xC5><0x99> nezm<0xC4><0x9B>nila.
Trinidad, located between the sea and the Escambray mountain range, is a place so far apart that even in the 1950s of the last century, there was no road that would connect this region with the rest of the country.
This isolation allowed him to stay on his side.
We were not building anything, and that is why we were not demolishing anything either, everyone was content to have a roof over their heads.
If you have more time in Trinidad than an afternoon, then it is worth visiting also some interesting places in the area, such as the Playa Ancón beach or the Sugar Valley.
Then, in the evening, it is customary to go to the Casa de la Música which gets alive after sunset and where the music only gets calm in the early morning.
Baracoa
