What insurance is right for me?
Automobile insurance, which covers the driver against possible claims, involves a significant expense that will depend on a variety of factors, such as age, sex, the age of the driver's licence, marital status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use of it, among others.
Having a car is the main thing.
Choosing the right car insurance is even harder than choosing the vehicle model.
And it is that choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the model of the vehicle.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insurer.
This compromise is realized by an insurance contract, which establishes that the company receives the value of the premium granted and in return becomes responsible for the obligation to pay compensation in the event of a claim.
The premium is the insurance price, which is determined by taking into account a variety of factors, such as age, sex, age of the driver's licence, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or use, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices based on statistics, so that the higher the likelihood of an accident, the higher the odds to be paid.
This is why people over the age of 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, as statistics show that these people have a lower claim rate due to their caution.
Similarly, using censuses, the companies concluded that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use of the vehicle will affect the frequency, and therefore the likelihood of an accident.
By increasing the frequency, the probability increases.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when determining the price of the premium.
This is why the driver must carefully study the situation to choose the car insurance that best suits his profile.
Here we will present the most significant variables when choosing one or the other type of insurance, so that it, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insurer, offers him a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 face various drawbacks when contracting with affordable insurance, as may be the low experience in driving and the seniority of the driver's license.
While the ideal to be well insured is insurance at all risk, there are other, more economical options.
The most forward-thinking drivers can opt for all-risk insurance with deductible, so that they get insurance coverage at all risks but at a more affordable price.
This form of agreement implies that the customer pays a portion of the amount of the claim.
"The portion of the claim amount that the customer pays will be determined based on the value of the premium, which will be higher the amount will be lower," says Luis Noguera, the head in Spain of First Europa, an online insurance broker.
Another option is extended third-party insurance, so that the customer provides protection to deal with damages caused to third parties, but by those caused on his own car.
In addition, it would be covered against theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
Advice.
If you are under the age of 25 try to be cautious and avoid claims as much as possible, since this will affect the bonus, which can reduce the cost of insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction in the basic rate that the company has.
On the contrary, a sanction is an increase in the basic tariff.
"The bonuses and sanctions will depend on the company and its profit.
If the company has had a good year it will be able to afford to increase the bonuses ", clarifies Noguera.
Beyond the age of 25, it becomes easier for drivers to enter into an insurance contract, since the rate of claims is reduced thanks to the accumulated experience.
It is for this reason that it is better to choose insurance all risk with deductible.
"Normally young people cannot take advantage of the experience previously acquired after an accident," says the director of the European company in Spain and adds that the majority of accidents occur during the second year of driving, once the 'fear of the novice' has passed.
However, if the client is married but has no children yet, it is preferable that he negotiates insurance at all risk, as long as his economic situation allows him.
Marriages with children are considered by insurers to be the people with the lowest claim rate, because the surcharges will be lower.
In this case the best insurance would be insurance at all risk with deductible (may be 300 euros), or an extended third-party insurance from the third year of the life of the vehicle when the insured has a high level of bonus.
“They have more casual driving and they have greater purchasing power to afford the luxury to assume a larger amount of franchises,” said Luis Noguera.
For retirees, insurance at all risk with a deductible is preferable (being this one of 150 euros), or an extended third-party insurance when the insurer has a high level of bonus.
It must be said that auto insurance is important, not only because it covers the driver in the face of possible accidents, but also because it represents a significant expense, which is why it is essential to properly study the insurance that suits us most according to our personal situation.
